Detailed Description

Abstract superclass for the parser threads in one server.

The subclasses of this class should parse the data from the client (of any kind), create a request, insert that into the server, wait for the answer, format outdata and send that back to the client.

bool ParserThread::checkService (  const ClientSetting *  clientSetting,
const HttpInterfaceRequest *  httpRequest,
OperationType::operationType  operationType,
PurchaseOptions &  purchaseOptions,
set< MC2String > &  checkedServiceIDs,
const MC2Coordinate &  serviceLocation = MC2Coordinate(),
uint32  topRegionID = MAX_UINT32,
LangType::language_t  clientLang = LangTypes::english,
bool  mayUseCachedCheckResult = false
) 
 

Checks if the client is allowed to consume the service.

It will return true if the client is allowed to use the service and and false if the user can not or if something went wrong in the communication. If the user can not consume the service the packages will be set to the url for the client to present to the webserver.

Parameters:
clientSetting The setting to check.
httpRequest The http request.
operationType The type of service to consume.
url An url with possible packages to purchase if the user is not allowed to consume the service.
checkedServiceIDs A set with the service ids we have already queried, used to avoid rechecking.
serviceLocation The cordinate location for the service in case a top region is not sent with the request.
topRegionID The top region id for the service requested.
clientLang The client's language type. Default is set to English.
mayUseCachedCheckResult If the result of a previous check may be used as return for this call.
Returns:
True if the client can consume the service, false if not. If false is returned there are two possible outcomes. One where something went wrong in the communication towards external access authority and then the url will be empty, otherwhise and url will be created with the available packages to purchase.
